43 bool JointConstraintSampler::configure(const moveit_msgs::Constraints& constr)
44 {
45  // construct the constraints
46  std::vector<kinematic_constraints::JointConstraint> jc;
47  for (const moveit_msgs::JointConstraint& joint_constraint : constr.joint_constraints)
48  {
49  kinematic_constraints::JointConstraint j(scene_->getRobotModel());
50  if (j.configure(joint_constraint))
51  jc.push_back(j);
52  }
53 
54  return jc.empty() ? false : configure(jc);
55 }

57 bool JointConstraintSampler::configure(const std::vector<kinematic_constraints::JointConstraint>& jc)
58 {
59  clear();
60 
61  if (!jmg_)
62  {
63  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "NULL group specified for constraint sampler");
64  return false;
65  }
66 
67  // find and keep the constraints that operate on the group we sample
68  // also keep bounds for joints as convenient
69  std::map<std::string, JointInfo> bound_data;
70  bool some_valid_constraint = false;
71  for (const kinematic_constraints::JointConstraint& joint_constraint : jc)
72  {
73  if (!joint_constraint.enabled())
74  continue;
75 
76  const moveit::core::JointModel* jm = joint_constraint.getJointModel();
77  if (!jmg_->hasJointModel(jm->getName()))
78  continue;
79 
80  some_valid_constraint = true;
81 
82  const moveit::core::VariableBounds& joint_bounds = jm->getVariableBounds(joint_constraint.getJointVariableName());
83  JointInfo ji;
84  std::map<std::string, JointInfo>::iterator it = bound_data.find(joint_constraint.getJointVariableName());
85  if (it != bound_data.end())
86  ji = it->second;
87  else
88  ji.index_ = jmg_->getVariableGroupIndex(joint_constraint.getJointVariableName());
89  ji.potentiallyAdjustMinMaxBounds(
90  std::max(joint_bounds.min_position_,
91  joint_constraint.getDesiredJointPosition() - joint_constraint.getJointToleranceBelow()),
92  std::min(joint_bounds.max_position_,
93  joint_constraint.getDesiredJointPosition() + joint_constraint.getJointToleranceAbove()));
94 
95  ROS_DEBUG_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "Bounds for %s JointConstraint are %g %g",
96  joint_constraint.getJointVariableName().c_str(), ji.min_bound_, ji.max_bound_);
97 
98  if (ji.min_bound_ > ji.max_bound_ + std::numeric_limits<double>::epsilon())
99  {
100  std::stringstream cs;
101  joint_constraint.print(cs);
102  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers",
103  "The constraints for joint '%s' are such that "
104  "there are no possible values for the joint: min_bound: %g, max_bound: %g. Failing.\n",
105  jm->getName().c_str(), ji.min_bound_, ji.max_bound_);
106  clear();
107  return false;
108  }
109  bound_data[joint_constraint.getJointVariableName()] = ji;
110  }
111 
112  if (!some_valid_constraint)
113  {
114  ROS_WARN_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "No valid joint constraints");
115  return false;
116  }
117 
118  for (std::pair<const std::string, JointInfo>& it : bound_data)
119  bounds_.push_back(it.second);
120 
121  // get a separate list of joints that are not bounded; we will sample these randomly
122  const std::vector<const moveit::core::JointModel*>& joints = jmg_->getJointModels();
123  for (const moveit::core::JointModel* joint : joints)
124  if (bound_data.find(joint->getName()) == bound_data.end() && joint->getVariableCount() > 0 &&
125  joint->getMimic() == nullptr)
126  {
127  // check if all the vars of the joint are found in bound_data instead
128  const std::vector<std::string>& vars = joint->getVariableNames();
129  if (vars.size() > 1)
130  {
131  bool all_found = true;
132  for (const std::string& var : vars)
133  if (bound_data.find(var) == bound_data.end())
134  {
135  all_found = false;
136  break;
137  }
138  if (all_found)
139  continue;
140  }
141  unbounded_.push_back(joint);
142  // Get the first variable name of this joint and find its index position in the planning group
143  uindex_.push_back(jmg_->getVariableGroupIndex(vars[0]));
144  }
145  values_.resize(jmg_->getVariableCount());
146  is_valid_ = true;
147  return true;
148 }

150 bool JointConstraintSampler::sample(moveit::core::RobotState& state,
151  const moveit::core::RobotState& /* reference_state */,
152  unsigned int /* max_attempts */)
153 {
154  if (!is_valid_)
155  {
156  ROS_WARN_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "JointConstraintSampler not configured, won't sample");
157  return false;
158  }
159 
160  // sample the unbounded joints first (in case some joint variables are bounded)
161  std::vector<double> v;
162  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < unbounded_.size(); ++i)
163  {
164  v.resize(unbounded_[i]->getVariableCount());
165  unbounded_[i]->getVariableRandomPositions(random_number_generator_, &v[0]);
166  for (std::size_t j = 0; j < v.size(); ++j)
167  values_[uindex_[i] + j] = v[j];
168  }
169 
170  // enforce the constraints for the constrained components (could be all of them)
171  for (const JointInfo& bound : bounds_)
172  values_[bound.index_] = random_number_generator_.uniformReal(bound.min_bound_, bound.max_bound_);
173 
174  state.setJointGroupPositions(jmg_, values_);
175 
176  // we are always successful
177  return true;
178 }

180 bool JointConstraintSampler::project(moveit::core::RobotState& state, unsigned int max_attempts)
181 {
182  return sample(state, state, max_attempts);

239 bool IKConstraintSampler::configure(const IKSamplingPose& sp)
240 {
241  clear();
242  if (!sp.position_constraint_ && !sp.orientation_constraint_)
243  return false;
244  if ((!sp.orientation_constraint_ && !sp.position_constraint_->enabled()) ||
245  (!sp.position_constraint_ && !sp.orientation_constraint_->enabled()) ||
246  (sp.position_constraint_ && sp.orientation_constraint_ && !sp.position_constraint_->enabled() &&
247  !sp.orientation_constraint_->enabled()))
248  {
249  ROS_WARN_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "No enabled constraints in sampling pose");
250  return false;
251  }
252 
253  sampling_pose_ = sp;
254  ik_timeout_ = jmg_->getDefaultIKTimeout();
255  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_ && sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_)
256  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getLinkModel()->getName() !=
257  sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getLinkModel()->getName())
258  {
259  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers",
260  "Position and orientation constraints need to be specified for the same link "
261  "in order to use IK-based sampling");
262  return false;
263  }
264 
265  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_ && sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->mobileReferenceFrame())
266  frame_depends_.push_back(sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getReferenceFrame());
267  if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_ && sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->mobileReferenceFrame())
268  frame_depends_.push_back(sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getReferenceFrame());
269  kb_ = jmg_->getSolverInstance();
270  if (!kb_)
271  {
272  ROS_WARN_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "No solver instance in setup");
273  is_valid_ = false;
274  return false;
275  }
276  is_valid_ = loadIKSolver();
277  return is_valid_;
278 }

280 bool IKConstraintSampler::configure(const moveit_msgs::Constraints& constr)
281 {
282  for (std::size_t p = 0; p < constr.position_constraints.size(); ++p)
283  for (std::size_t o = 0; o < constr.orientation_constraints.size(); ++o)
284  if (constr.position_constraints[p].link_name == constr.orientation_constraints[o].link_name)
285  {
286  kinematic_constraints::PositionConstraintPtr pc(
287  new kinematic_constraints::PositionConstraint(scene_->getRobotModel()));
288  kinematic_constraints::OrientationConstraintPtr oc(
289  new kinematic_constraints::OrientationConstraint(scene_->getRobotModel()));
290  if (pc->configure(constr.position_constraints[p], scene_->getTransforms()) &&
291  oc->configure(constr.orientation_constraints[o], scene_->getTransforms()))
292  return configure(IKSamplingPose(pc, oc));
293  }
294 
295  for (const moveit_msgs::PositionConstraint& position_constraint : constr.position_constraints)
296  {
297  kinematic_constraints::PositionConstraintPtr pc(
298  new kinematic_constraints::PositionConstraint(scene_->getRobotModel()));
299  if (pc->configure(position_constraint, scene_->getTransforms()))
300  return configure(IKSamplingPose(pc));
301  }
302 
303  for (const moveit_msgs::OrientationConstraint& orientation_constraint : constr.orientation_constraints)
304  {
305  kinematic_constraints::OrientationConstraintPtr oc(
306  new kinematic_constraints::OrientationConstraint(scene_->getRobotModel()));
307  if (oc->configure(orientation_constraint, scene_->getTransforms()))
308  return configure(IKSamplingPose(oc));
309  }
310  return false;
311 }

313 double IKConstraintSampler::getSamplingVolume() const
314 {
315  double v = 1.0;
316  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_)
317  {
318  const std::vector<bodies::BodyPtr>& constraint_regions =
319  sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getConstraintRegions();
320  double vol = 0;
321  for (const bodies::BodyPtr& constraint_region : constraint_regions)
322  vol += constraint_region->computeVolume();
323  if (!constraint_regions.empty())
324  v *= vol;
325  }
326 
327  if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_)
328  v *= sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getXAxisTolerance() *
329  sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getYAxisTolerance() *
330  sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getZAxisTolerance();
331  return v;
332 }

334 const std::string& IKConstraintSampler::getLinkName() const
335 {
336  if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_)
337  return sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getLinkModel()->getName();
338  return sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getLinkModel()->getName();
339 }

341 bool IKConstraintSampler::loadIKSolver()
342 {
343  if (!kb_)
344  {
345  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "No IK solver");
346  return false;
347  }
348 
349  // check if we need to transform the request into the coordinate frame expected by IK
350  ik_frame_ = kb_->getBaseFrame();
351  transform_ik_ = !moveit::core::Transforms::sameFrame(ik_frame_, jmg_->getParentModel().getModelFrame());
352  if (!ik_frame_.empty() && ik_frame_[0] == '/')
353  ik_frame_.erase(ik_frame_.begin());
354  if (transform_ik_)
355  if (!jmg_->getParentModel().hasLinkModel(ik_frame_))
356  {
357  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers",
358  "The IK solver expects requests in frame '%s' but this frame is not known to the sampler. "
359  "Ignoring transformation (IK may fail)",
360  ik_frame_.c_str());
361  transform_ik_ = false;
362  }
363 
364  // check if IK is performed for the desired link
365  bool wrong_link = false;
366  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_)
367  {
368  const moveit::core::LinkModel* lm = sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getLinkModel();
369  if (!moveit::core::Transforms::sameFrame(kb_->getTipFrame(), lm->getName()))
370  {
371  wrong_link = true;
372  const moveit::core::LinkTransformMap& fixed_links = lm->getAssociatedFixedTransforms();
373  for (const std::pair<const moveit::core::LinkModel* const, Eigen::Isometry3d>& fixed_link : fixed_links)
374  if (moveit::core::Transforms::sameFrame(fixed_link.first->getName(), kb_->getTipFrame()))
375  {
376  eef_to_ik_tip_transform_ = fixed_link.second; // valid isometry by contract
377  need_eef_to_ik_tip_transform_ = true;
378  wrong_link = false;
379  break;
380  }
381  }
382  }
383 
384  if (!wrong_link && sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_)
385  {
386  const moveit::core::LinkModel* lm = sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getLinkModel();
387  if (!moveit::core::Transforms::sameFrame(kb_->getTipFrame(), lm->getName()))
388  {
389  wrong_link = true;
390  const moveit::core::LinkTransformMap& fixed_links = lm->getAssociatedFixedTransforms();
391  for (const std::pair<const moveit::core::LinkModel* const, Eigen::Isometry3d>& fixed_link : fixed_links)
392  if (moveit::core::Transforms::sameFrame(fixed_link.first->getName(), kb_->getTipFrame()))
393  {
394  eef_to_ik_tip_transform_ = fixed_link.second; // valid isometry by contract
395  need_eef_to_ik_tip_transform_ = true;
396  wrong_link = false;
397  break;
398  }
399  }
400  }
401 
402  if (wrong_link)
403  {
404  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers",
405  "IK cannot be performed for link '%s'. The solver can report IK solutions for link '%s'.",
406  sampling_pose_.position_constraint_ ?
407  sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getLinkModel()->getName().c_str() :
408  sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getLinkModel()->getName().c_str(),
409  kb_->getTipFrame().c_str());
410  return false;
411  }
412  return true;
413 }

415 bool IKConstraintSampler::samplePose(Eigen::Vector3d& pos, Eigen::Quaterniond& quat, const moveit::core::RobotState& ks,
416  unsigned int max_attempts)
417 {
418  if (ks.dirtyLinkTransforms())
419  {
420  // samplePose below requires accurate transforms
421  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers",
422  "IKConstraintSampler received dirty robot state, but valid transforms are required. "
423  "Failing.");
424  return false;
425  }
426 
427  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_)
428  {
429  const std::vector<bodies::BodyPtr>& b = sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getConstraintRegions();
430  if (!b.empty())
431  {
432  bool found = false;
433  std::size_t k = random_number_generator_.uniformInteger(0, b.size() - 1);
434  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < b.size(); ++i)
435  if (b[(i + k) % b.size()]->samplePointInside(random_number_generator_, max_attempts, pos))
436  {
437  found = true;
438  break;
439  }
440  if (!found)
441  {
442  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "Unable to sample a point inside the constraint region");
443  return false;
444  }
445  }
446  else
447  {
448  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "Unable to sample a point inside the constraint region. "
449  "Constraint region is empty when it should not be.");
450  return false;
451  }
452 
453  // if this constraint is with respect a mobile frame, we need to convert this rotation to the root frame of the
454  // model
455  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->mobileReferenceFrame())
456  pos = ks.getFrameTransform(sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getReferenceFrame()) * pos;
457  }
458  else
459  {
460  // do FK for rand state
461  moveit::core::RobotState temp_state(ks);
462  temp_state.setToRandomPositions(jmg_);
463  pos = temp_state.getGlobalLinkTransform(sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getLinkModel()).translation();
464  }
465 
466  if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_)
467  {
468  // sample a rotation matrix within the allowed bounds
469  double angle_x =
470  2.0 * (random_number_generator_.uniform01() - 0.5) *
471  (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getXAxisTolerance() - std::numeric_limits<double>::epsilon());
472  double angle_y =
473  2.0 * (random_number_generator_.uniform01() - 0.5) *
474  (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getYAxisTolerance() - std::numeric_limits<double>::epsilon());
475  double angle_z =
476  2.0 * (random_number_generator_.uniform01() - 0.5) *
477  (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getZAxisTolerance() - std::numeric_limits<double>::epsilon());
478 
479  Eigen::Isometry3d diff;
480  if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getParameterizationType() ==
481  moveit_msgs::OrientationConstraint::XYZ_EULER_ANGLES)
482  {
483  diff = Eigen::Isometry3d(Eigen::AngleAxisd(angle_x, Eigen::Vector3d::UnitX()) *
484  Eigen::AngleAxisd(angle_y, Eigen::Vector3d::UnitY()) *
485  Eigen::AngleAxisd(angle_z, Eigen::Vector3d::UnitZ()));
486  }
487  else if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getParameterizationType() ==
488  moveit_msgs::OrientationConstraint::ROTATION_VECTOR)
489  {
490  Eigen::Vector3d rotation_vector(angle_x, angle_y, angle_z);
491  diff = Eigen::Isometry3d(Eigen::AngleAxisd(rotation_vector.norm(), rotation_vector.normalized()));
492  }
493  else
494  {
495  /* The parameterization type should be validated in configure, so this should never happen. */
496  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED("default_constraint_samplers",
497  "The parameterization type for the orientation constraints is invalid.");
498  }
499 
500  // diff is isometry by construction
501  // getDesiredRotationMatrix() returns a valid rotation matrix by contract
502  // reqr has thus to be a valid isometry
503  Eigen::Isometry3d reqr(sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getDesiredRotationMatrix() * diff.linear());
504  quat = Eigen::Quaterniond(reqr.linear()); // reqr is isometry, so quat has to be normalized
505 
506  // if this constraint is with respect a mobile frame, we need to convert this rotation to the root frame of the
507  // model
508  if (sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->mobileReferenceFrame())
509  {
510  // getFrameTransform() returns a valid isometry by contract
511  const Eigen::Isometry3d& t = ks.getFrameTransform(sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->getReferenceFrame());
512  // rt is isometry by construction
513  Eigen::Isometry3d rt(t.linear() * quat);
514  quat = Eigen::Quaterniond(rt.linear()); // rt is isometry, so quat has to be normalized
515  }
516  }
517  else
518  {
519  // sample a random orientation
520  double q[4];
521  random_number_generator_.quaternion(q);
522  quat = Eigen::Quaterniond(q[3], q[0], q[1], q[2]); // quat is normalized by contract
523  }
524 
525  // if there is an offset, we need to undo the induced rotation in the sampled transform origin (point)
526  if (sampling_pose_.position_constraint_ && sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->hasLinkOffset())
527  // the rotation matrix that corresponds to the desired orientation
528  pos = pos - quat * sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->getLinkOffset();
529 
530  return true;
531 }

535 void samplingIkCallbackFnAdapter(moveit::core::RobotState* state, const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* jmg,
536  const moveit::core::GroupStateValidityCallbackFn& constraint,
537  const geometry_msgs::Pose& /*unused*/, const std::vector<double>& ik_sol,
538  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes& error_code)
539 {
540  const std::vector<unsigned int>& bij = jmg->getKinematicsSolverJointBijection();
541  std::vector<double> solution(bij.size());
542  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < bij.size(); ++i)
543  solution[i] = ik_sol[bij[i]];
544  if (constraint(state, jmg, &solution[0]))
545  error_code.val = moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes::SUCCESS;
546  else
547  error_code.val = moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes::NO_IK_SOLUTION;
548 }
549 } // namespace

551 bool IKConstraintSampler::sample(moveit::core::RobotState& state, const moveit::core::RobotState& reference_state,
552  unsigned int max_attempts)
553 {
554  return sampleHelper(state, reference_state, max_attempts, false);
555 }
556 
557 bool IKConstraintSampler::sampleHelper(moveit::core::RobotState& state, const moveit::core::RobotState& reference_state,
558  unsigned int max_attempts, bool project)
559 {
560  if (!is_valid_)
561  {
562  ROS_WARN_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "IKConstraintSampler not configured, won't sample");
563  return false;
564  }
565 
566  kinematics::KinematicsBase::IKCallbackFn adapted_ik_validity_callback;
567  if (group_state_validity_callback_)
568  adapted_ik_validity_callback =
569  boost::bind(&samplingIkCallbackFnAdapter, &state, jmg_, group_state_validity_callback_, _1, _2, _3);
570 
571  for (unsigned int a = 0; a < max_attempts; ++a)
572  {
573  // sample a point in the constraint region
574  Eigen::Vector3d point;
575  Eigen::Quaterniond quat; // quat is normalized by contract
576  if (!samplePose(point, quat, reference_state, max_attempts))
577  {
578  if (verbose_)
579  ROS_INFO_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "IK constraint sampler was unable to produce a pose to run IK for");
580  return false;
581  }
582 
583  // we now have the transform we wish to perform IK for, in the planning frame
584  if (transform_ik_)
585  {
586  // we need to convert this transform to the frame expected by the IK solver
587  // both the planning frame and the frame for the IK are assumed to be robot links
588  Eigen::Isometry3d ikq(Eigen::Translation3d(point) * quat); // valid isometry by construction
589  // getFrameTransform() returns a valid isometry by contract
590  ikq = reference_state.getFrameTransform(ik_frame_).inverse() * ikq; // valid isometry * valid isometry
591  point = ikq.translation();
592  quat = Eigen::Quaterniond(ikq.linear()); // ikq is isometry, so quat is normalized
593  }
594 
595  if (need_eef_to_ik_tip_transform_)
596  {
597  // After sampling the pose needs to be transformed to the ik chain tip
598  Eigen::Isometry3d ikq(Eigen::Translation3d(point) * quat); // valid isometry by construction
599  ikq = ikq * eef_to_ik_tip_transform_; // eef_to_ik_tip_transform_ is valid isometry (checked in loadIKSolver())
600  point = ikq.translation();
601  quat = Eigen::Quaterniond(ikq.linear()); // ikq is isometry, so quat is normalized
602  }
603 
604  geometry_msgs::Pose ik_query;
605  ik_query.position.x = point.x();
606  ik_query.position.y = point.y();
607  ik_query.position.z = point.z();
608  ik_query.orientation.x = quat.x();
609  ik_query.orientation.y = quat.y();
610  ik_query.orientation.z = quat.z();
611  ik_query.orientation.w = quat.w();
612 
613  if (callIK(ik_query, adapted_ik_validity_callback, ik_timeout_, state, project && a == 0))
614  return true;
615  }
616  return false;
617 }
618 
619 bool IKConstraintSampler::project(moveit::core::RobotState& state, unsigned int max_attempts)
620 {
621  return sampleHelper(state, state, max_attempts, true);
622 }
623 
624 bool IKConstraintSampler::validate(moveit::core::RobotState& state) const
625 {
626  state.update();
627  return (!sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_ ||
628  sampling_pose_.orientation_constraint_->decide(state, verbose_).satisfied) &&
629  (!sampling_pose_.position_constraint_ ||
630  sampling_pose_.position_constraint_->decide(state, verbose_).satisfied);
631 }
632 
633 bool IKConstraintSampler::callIK(const geometry_msgs::Pose& ik_query,
634  const kinematics::KinematicsBase::IKCallbackFn& adapted_ik_validity_callback,
635  double timeout, moveit::core::RobotState& state, bool use_as_seed)
636 {
637  const std::vector<unsigned int>& ik_joint_bijection = jmg_->getKinematicsSolverJointBijection();
638  std::vector<double> seed(ik_joint_bijection.size(), 0.0);
639  std::vector<double> vals;
640 
641  if (use_as_seed)
642  state.copyJointGroupPositions(jmg_, vals);
643  else
644  // sample a seed value
645  jmg_->getVariableRandomPositions(random_number_generator_, vals);
646 
647  assert(vals.size() == ik_joint_bijection.size());
648  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < ik_joint_bijection.size(); ++i)
649  seed[i] = vals[ik_joint_bijection[i]];
650 
651  std::vector<double> ik_sol;
652  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes error;
653 
654  if (adapted_ik_validity_callback ?
655  kb_->searchPositionIK(ik_query, seed, timeout, ik_sol, adapted_ik_validity_callback, error) :
656  kb_->searchPositionIK(ik_query, seed, timeout, ik_sol, error))
657  {
658  assert(ik_sol.size() == ik_joint_bijection.size());
659  std::vector<double> solution(ik_joint_bijection.size());
660  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < ik_joint_bijection.size(); ++i)
661  solution[ik_joint_bijection[i]] = ik_sol[i];
662  state.setJointGroupPositions(jmg_, solution);
663 
664  return validate(state);
665  }
666  else
667  {
668  if (error.val != moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes::NO_IK_SOLUTION &&
669  error.val != moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes::INVALID_ROBOT_STATE &&
670  error.val != moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes::TIMED_OUT)
671  ROS_ERROR_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "IK solver failed with error %d", error.val);
672  else if (verbose_)
673  ROS_INFO_NAMED("constraint_samplers", "IK failed");
674  }
675  return false;
676 }
677 
678 } // end of namespace constraint_samplers
